
[1]ravishment

   RAV'ISHMENT, n.

   1. The act of forcing a woman to carnal connection; forcible violation
   of chastity.

   2. Rapture; transport of delight; ecstasy; pleasing violence of the
   mind or senses.

   All things joy with ravishment attracted by thy beauty still to gaze.

   3. The act of carrying away; abduction; as the ravishment of children
   from their parents, of a ward from his guardian, or of a wife from her
   husband.
